Emancipation was not only important to free the slaves from their nasty work of picking the sugar cane for the white men, but it also started the process for the end of discrimination between the white and colored people. The country is a constitutional monarchy and Elizabeth II is the reigning Queen of Barbados who ensures for the country's constitutional governmental system. There is a prime-minister of Barbados and is from the Barbados Labor Party since 1994 and is currently called Owen Arthur. The members of the lower house represent each of the sixteen constituencies of the country which is equal to 30 members in the house.Although there is bicameral system of government in the country, the constitution ensures that the upper house should not block the decisions taken in the lower house. The people elect or appoint the members of the two houses and the law-making body.The voting voting for the general elections takes place every five years.
